He said in the document that he had been valuable to the firm because he was plugged in in this town and knows the defense business pretty well. In the deposition, Tower said that Rockwell paid him $120000 a year but said he was underutilized by the firm. In the divorce papers, however, Tower said that he went to work for British Aerospace Inc. Tower aides said they had no comment on the matter. In the deposition, Tower said he represented the firm on a range of military programs and was paid $8000 a month. 